<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFBCFF9BFF20FD71FA81FC3E" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FD71FB86FD3A" blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1077]" box="[199,1126,690,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF20FD71FEB9FD3B" bold="true" box="[199,345,690,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Description.</emphasis>
Similar in appearance to other members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFC51FD70FB80FD3A" authorityName="Zakhvatkin" authorityYear="1953" box="[950,1120,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFC51FD70FB80FD3A" box="[950,1120,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FD14FDFEFC76" blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
Aedeagal processes in posterior view at bases smoothly bent basad and diverging at angle slightly less than 90 
<superScript id="7C033C50FFBCFF9BFA6AFD14FA75FD12" attach="none" box="[1421,1429,727,741]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">o</superScript>
, without additional branches or denticles, straight or with tips only slightly bent outwards (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFB77FD38FAFBFCE2" box="[1168,1307,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 24–25</figureCitation>
). Length of processes averages 1/5–1/6 of shaft length. Aedeagal shaft S-curved in lateral view, with processes either parallel to or slightly bent towards shaft (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFE0DFC80FD93FCA9" box="[490,627,835,862]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 26–27</figureCitation>
). Gonopore somewhat distant from aedeagal apex, postgonoporal part of shaft distinctly narrowed (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFE5AFCA4FDF1FC76" box="[445,529,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FC48FA81FC3E" blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<location id="8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFF20FC48FEB0FC52" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DF200EFFBCFF9BFF70FE3DFA61FBC2:8EA9C7C3FFBCFF9BFF20FC48FEB0FC52" box="[199,336,907,933]" name="Investigated" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" stateProvince="Irkutsk">Investigated</location>
specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="49B25FFAFFBCFF9BFDECFC48FD48FC52" box="[523,680,907,933]" country="Russia" name="Irkutsk" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Irkutsk Oblast</collectingRegion>
are indistinguishable from 
<typeStatus id="54CD2FBAFFBCFF9BFC31FC48FBE6FC52" box="[982,1030,907,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
specimens from Yakutia in aedeagus shape (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFF01FC6CFE0AFC3E" box="[230,490,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 24–28 and 29–31</figureCitation>
) in spite of the fact that the distance between these localities exceeds 
<quantity id="4C8E3CFDFFBCFF9BFB10FC6CFABDFC3E" box="[1271,1373,943,969]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" unit="km" value="1800.0">1800 km</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFBCFF9BFF20FC11FA61FBC2" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FC11FA61FBC2" blockId="4.[151,1437,618,1077]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF20FC11FE81FC1B" bold="true" box="[199,353,978,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Distribution.</emphasis>
Until now 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFE05FC10FD9FFC1A" authorityName="Emelyanov" authorityYear="1976" box="[482,639,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinokurovi">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFE05FC10FD9FFC1A" box="[482,639,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. vinokurovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered endemic to Yakutia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFBC4FC10FABEFC1A" author="Sivtsev, V. V. &amp; Vinokurov, N. N." box="[1059,1374,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4131" refString="Sivtsev, V. V. &amp; Vinokurov, N. N. (2002) Leafhoppers (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) of Yakutia. Siberian subdivision of the Russian Academy of Sciences Publ., Novosibirsk, 136 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="2002">Sivtsev &amp; Vinokurov, 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The finding of this species in the steppe enclave in the Lower Angara River Valley significantly expands its known distribution. Further records of this species in local steppe areas in river valleys of Eastern Siberia can be expected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
